  "text": "to the following variable coefficient BO (vBO) equation Here R(t) = t0 t+t0 . Equation (6.2) has the left boundary condition fixed at φ − = 1, while the right boundary condition φ + = 0 stays the same as in the original sBO equation. In order to solve Eq. (6.2) numerically (see also [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ) we differentiate with respect to η and define φ η = z to get z t + R(t) (zφ) η + ǫH (z ηη ) = 0.",
